(firstQuint)Effect of the Enteric Hormone Glucagon-Like Peptide (GLP-2) on the Intestinal Blood Flow in Patients With Short Bowel Syndrome.

 previous studies have shown that GLP-2 increases mesenteric blow flow, we wish to examine the effect of subcutaneus GLP-2 on patients with short bowl syndrome.

 The patients will single blinded been given 450 nmol GLP-2 and isotonic saline in order to act as their own reference.

